description.text:
When printing raftless it can be helpful to add a bounding box type extrusion on the first layer of the print, kind of like nophead uses (see <a rel="nofollow" href="http://hydraraptor.blogspot.com/2010/01/hot-metal-and-serendipity.html" >http://hydraraptor.blogspot.com/2010/01/hot-metal-and-serendipity.html</a><br />
). This outline gives the extruder some extra time to begin extruding properly before beginning your object, and so you get an early verification of where your object<br />
will sit on the platform.  Being a plugin you can turn the outline on and off as part of your usual skeinforge profiles.
